olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 tin sweetcorn
1 tin black beans
1 sachet Mexican Fiesta spice blend
1 packet tomato paste
¼ cup water
½ tbs brown sugar
20 g plant-based butter
1 packet enchilada sauce
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Plant-Based Mayo
1 packet beef mince

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop garlic. Grate the carrot.
• Drain the sweetcorn. Drain and rinse 1/2 the black beans.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook carrot and beef mince, breaking beef up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• SPICY! You may find the spice blend hot! Add less if sensitive to heat. Add garlic, Mexican Fiesta spice blend and tomato paste, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add beans, the water, brown sugar and butter and cook, stirring, until thickened, 2-3 minutes.
• Remove from heat. Stir through 1/2 the enchilada sauce, until combined. Season to taste

• Lay mini flour tortillas on a flat surface. Spoon bean filling down the centre of each tortilla.
• Roll tortillas up tightly and place, seam-side down, evenly spaced on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
• Bake taquitos until golden and starting to crisp, 8-10 minutes.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop baby spinach leaves.
• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to mediumhigh heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook sweetcorn until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the kernels are “popping” out.

• To the bowl with the corn, add baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Divide beef and black bean taquitos between plates.
• Top with remaining enchilada sauce and corn salsa.
• Drizzle over plant-based mayo. Enjoy!